Details

Job Posting Title:   Engineer/Konstruktör Simulation / Simulering level 2 [EE]
Description:   Electrical design leader within Testing Technology and Metrology

Where you’ll belong
We are looking for an Electrical design leader with good skills within metrology, design, and network to join our Testing Technology & Metrology team within R&D at Volvo Cars Headquarters in Gothenburg.

At Testing Technology & Metrology we establish and develop relationships with test engineers with almost all system areas of the vehicle as well as building as well as building an understanding of the technology within those areas. We provide metrology expertise, solutions for testing, lending of instrumentation, design and service of development tools and solutions for testing departments.

What you’ll do
You will be an electrical design leader for one existing system that needs to be updated. You will work with verification of the updated system and lead the progress in the project.
You will also be supporting our internal R&D organization and our customers/colleagues in their use of a wide range of metrology and testing tools, with a focus on measurement solutions in our electrical vehicles.
You will work closely with test engineers from the whole R&D, some of our close collaborating departments are Electric Powertrain, Active Safety, Chassis and Electrics/Electronics to find suitable measurement solutions for their needs.
Examples of development tools we work with are INCA, Vector and Dewesoft, and examples of communication protocols that we use are Ethernet, CAN, LIN and Flexray.

You and your skills
We see that you have a B. Sc. Degree or higher, in Mechatronics, Computer Engineering, Engineering Physics, Electrical Engineering or similar relevant experience. You have previous experience from a design leader role and good knowledge within metrology tools and techniques. You also have general automotive knowledge and a genuine interest in technology and problem solving. Driver´s license (B) is meritorious.

On a personal level, you are a person with high integrity and professionalism, who enjoys working in teams and to interact with people. You are a great communicator willing to share information with others. You have passion for the business and are performance-driven and will finish started tasks. Last, but not least, you will need a conceptual way of thinking and the ability to keep a holistic view to fully prosper.


